Phoenix 6 25.4.0

Hey folks! Hope everyone has had an amazing 2025 season and congratulations to the season winners 1323, 2910, 4272, 5026! We are announcing the release of version 25.4.0 of our Phoenix 6 library. With this release comes a long time ask of CANdle Phoenix 6 support.

Currently, this release contains CANdle feature-parity with Phoenix 6, and introductory support for LED control in Phoenix Tuner X (Tuner v2025.4.1.0). We have several CANdle and CANdle related Tuner features we are looking into for the 2026 season.

image1775×1109 107 KB

Another feature related to CANdle I want to bring to attention is it’s usefulness as a stable 5V 6A supply. This means you can power coprocessors such as a Raspberry Pi or Orange Pi 5 (one of our world demos was actually using a CANdle to provide 5V power to an Orange Pi 5 Pro)!

A full changelog for this release is available here and we encourage folks to sign up for our RSS feed, for notifications when releases are available.

just my thoughts, but if the CANdle is brought up to Phoenix 6 then phoenix tuner should have some sort of GUI on controlling the CANdle. on a serious note, thank you guys for this. we struggled with our CANdle multiple times this past year and in the end we had to just remove it so I’m hoping the bring up will allow us to debug a little easier so we can add back our LED feedback for the off-season.
